  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-11-13", 
    "text": "Taxpayer Justice Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to permit a husband and wife to file a combined return with separate income tax rates. Provides for: (1) a commission to study ways to simplify the U.S. income tax laws; (2) the use of mediation and alternative dispute resolution by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS); and (3) a Taxpayer Advisory Board composed of ordinary taxpayers to advise the IRS."
  }, 
